Medical Spending Account (FSA) & Dependent Care (DCA) Payroll Results

Organizations that offer Flexible Spending Accounts (FSA) and Dependent Care Accounts (DCA) must regularly extract employee deduction amounts from Oracle Fusion Payroll to:
Reconcile contributions with their FSA/DCA third-party administrator (TPA)
Generate funding files submitted to the benefits provider on each pay date
Audit that payroll processed the correct deduction amounts per employee per period

Flexible Spending Account (FSA)
Dependent Care Account (DCA)

Person / Employee
    └── Element Entry (pee)          ← benefit deduction enrolled
        └── Element Type (petf/pett) ← identifies FSA or DCA element
            └── Payroll Action (ppa) ← the payroll run event
                └── Time Period (ptpf) ← pay period with pay date
                    └── Rel Action (ppra) ← employee's run action
                        └── Run Result (prr) ← result for that element
                            └── Run Result Value (prrv) ← the $ amount
                                └── Input Value (pivf) ← value definition

The query retrieves employee details, payroll deduction amounts, and payroll check dates for a specific payroll period.

ParameterTypeRequiredDescription:P_PAYROLL_DATEVARCHAR2 (YYYY-MM-DD)YesThe pay date to extract results for. Must match ptpf.default_paydate exactly. Example: '2025-01-31'

